LOCAL FIX: Instead of storing an iterator, store the index of the element. Access the element using the index after the loop:
  size_t index = 2;
  // ... loop ...
  std::printf(\"element via index: %d\\n\", v[index]);

GLOBAL FIX: Adopt a design that avoids holding long-lived iterators or pointers to elements in containers that may be modified (reallocated). If references to elements are required, use a container that provides pointer stability (e.g., std::list, std::deque, or a container of smart pointers) or ensure that all modifications to the container occur in a scope where no such iterators are active."
"}

